<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="504" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d504">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW2" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <dateline>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-27">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 27, 1914</hi>.</date>
                            </dateline>
                            <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                            <p>504. Department’s telegram, October 9, regarding cargoes on vessels
                                destroyed by German cruisers. Interested persons represent to
                                Department German Government’s position this matter has important
                                effect on questions relating to insurance. Endeavor obtain early
                                reply from German Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>